  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.R1ew21i3luHJHfV5]{UM5 Ch.6: Gear} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.oW9iuEoxWvtPKvDo]{UM5 Ch.6: Tech Level 0-5}</p>\n<p>Thought once to be the realm of magic, the bender&nbsp;moves light around it, effectively making itself and its&nbsp;wearer invisible. The device, usually backpack-stored&nbsp;with a remote bracelet to operate it , creates a magnetic field, removing the target from sight, even from</p>\n<p>darkvision and infrared. As bending all light would necessarily prevent the user from seeing out of it, light of&nbsp;very specific wavelengths is allowed through the field,&nbsp;creating a ‘shimmer’ effect when the field moves (to the&nbsp;wearer, the world merely looks constantly twilit): sudden movements or attacks disrupt the field entirely.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>As an action, you become invisible. Each round uses&nbsp;a charge and the effect ends if you interact with something or someone or if you make any form of attack.</p>",
